Two people were injured and a bakkie extensively damaged after the vehicle crashed through a metal barrier and landed in a flood canal on the M25 in the vicinity of Ntuzuma, on Thursday morning. Members of Reaction Unit South Africa (Rusa) arrived on scene shortly after 6am and met with the driver who explained that he lost control of the bakkie after driving through a water patch. “Two of his passengers were injured. They were transported from the scene prior to the arrival of Reaction officers. The bakkie was extensively damaged in the accident,” said Rusa head, Prem Balram.